# What the Funan - Legal & Cultural Compliance Rules

## Overview
These rules MUST be followed at ALL times when developing "What the Funan" to ensure legal compliance and cultural sensitivity for Cambodia, Thailand, and Laos markets.

---

## CRITICAL RESTRICTIONS (VIOLATION = LEGAL RISK)

### Thailand Lèse-Majesté (Section 112) - PRISON RISK
- NEVER depict, reference, or include ANY Thai royalty (historical or modern)
- NEVER include imagery that could be interpreted as Thai royal symbols
- NEVER use names of Thai kings, queens, princes, or princesses
- NEVER create content that could be seen as mocking Thai monarchy
- This applies to ALL eras of Thai history

### Buddhist Content Restrictions
- NEVER place Buddha statues or images in combat scenarios
- NEVER show Buddha images being damaged, destroyed, or disrespected
- NEVER use monks as playable characters or combatants
- NEVER depict monks in violent or inappropriate situations
- NEVER sexualize any religious figures (apsaras in religious context)
- Buddha images must ALWAYS be shown respectfully and reverently
- Temple interiors with Buddha statues should not be battle arenas

### Gambling Restrictions
- NEVER implement real-money gambling mechanics
- NEVER create gacha/loot boxes with real money (virtual currency OK with disclosure)
- NEVER simulate casino games (slots, roulette, card gambling)
- Virtual currency systems must clearly state "no real-world value"
- Avoid mechanics that could be classified as gambling in these jurisdictions

### Political Content Restrictions
- NEVER reference modern political figures from Cambodia, Thailand, or Laos
- NEVER depict Khmer Rouge or genocide-related content
- NEVER reference current border disputes (especially Preah Vihear Temple)
- NEVER take sides in Cambodia-Thailand cultural disputes
- NEVER include content critical of Lao government or Communist Party

