2. When in doubt, choose the more conservative option
3. Flag any potential issues for cultural consultant review
4. Document all cultural/religious content decisions
5. Maintain audit trail of compliance reviews

## CONSEQUENCES OF VIOLATION

- Thailand: Lèse-majesté = 3-15 years imprisonment per offense
- Thailand: Content ban and company blacklist
- Cambodia: Content ban, potential legal action
- Laos: Criminal prosecution for anti-state content
- All regions: Reputation damage, market exclusion

